extends ../../layouts/layout-beta.pug

block content
  #content.section--primary
    .container
      h1 Object to the High Speed Rail (West Midlands – Crewe) Bill

      br
      div(data-browser='javascript')
        .status--highlight.theme--caution
          p JavaScript is currently switched off in your browser. Switch it on for a better experience.

      .status--highlight
        p The deadline is 5pm on 26 February 2018.

  section
    .container
      h2 Overview

      p Any individual, group of individuals, organisation or group of organisations affected by the High Speed Rail (West Midlands – Crewe) Bill can object to it.

      p To find out more about the Bill, visit the #[+link('https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/high-speed-two-limited', 'High Speed Two (HS2) Limited website')(target='_blank')]#[span.sr-only (This link will open in a new window)].

  section
    .container
      h2 Objecting to the Bill

      p To object to the High Speed Rail (West Midlands – Crewe) Bill you will need to download and complete our petition template. You can do this by petitioning on our website or by email, post or in person.

      p We will ask for your name, address and examples of how you are affected by the Bill.

      p The petition does not require any signatures.

  section
    .container
      h2 Contact details

      p We will ask you to tell us who should be contacted about your petition. This main contact can be you or someone else, for example a friend, family member or lawyer.

      p The main contact will receive all petition communications. They will usually be invited to give evidence about it to the  #[+link('http://www.parliament.uk/business/committees/committees-a-z/commons-select/high-speed-rail-west-midlands-crewe-bill-select-committee-commons', 'High Speed Rail (West Midlands – Crewe) Bill Committee')(target='_blank')]#[span.sr-only (This link will open in a new window)].

  section
    .container
      h2 After sending your petition

      ul.track--alternative
        li
          h3.typography--light Once we’ve received your petition we’ll ask you to pay a &pound;20 admin fee.
        li
          h3.typography--light We'll publish your petition on our website. This will include your name and address.
        li
          h3.typography--light We’ll send your petition to HS2 Ltd, who may contact you to discuss it.
        li
          h3.typography--light We’ll also send your petition to the Department for Transport (DfT). They can challenge it if they don’t believe you are affected by the Bill.
        li
          h3.typography--light You will usually be invited to give evidence to the committee about your petition. Hearings are scheduled for spring/summer 2018.

      .section--major
        div(data-browser='cookies')
          .status--highlight.theme--warning
            p #[+link('https://beta.parliament.uk/meta/cookie-policy', 'Cookies')] are currently blocked. Allow all cookies to petition online.
            p If you don’t want to allow all cookies, you can petition by email, post or in person.

        +buttonLink('page03.html', 'Petition on our website', 'btn--primary')(data-browser='button')
        +buttonLink('page02.html', 'Petition by email, post or in person', 'btn--primary--inverse')
